[Event "Baker Bridge - Negative Doubles and Cue-Bid Support"]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "1"]
[Dealer "N"]
[Vulnerable "None"]
[Deal "N:9.KQJ7.AK6.AQT54 AQJ73.T3.Q932.73 T86.A9642.84.K62 K542.85.JT75.J98"]
[Declarer "N"]
[Contract "4H"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "N"]
1C 1S X pass 4H pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 1, chOption: N, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:0, nBasis: 0, nRot: 0, useStandardVul: true"]
[VersionToken "418495dc73f85ae1b5a49d6f38bab3744a08906625a044f4bc8177cd1cc35837"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/negative_doubles"]
[Student "S"]
{SOUTH would have responded 1\H if EAST had not overcalled. 
But with only 8 points he cannot bid at the 2-level. The Negative Double solves his problem, 
giving this information to partner.

NORTH has good \Hs and enough points to bid game. 
Notice that if EAST had remained silent, SOUTH would have responded 1\H, 
and NORTH would have jumped to game.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "2"]
[Dealer "E"]
[Vulnerable "NS"]
[Deal "E:T97.K87.AK6.KJT4 Q83.AJT4.J54.765 AK62.93.972.Q982 J54.Q652.QT83.A3"]
[Declarer "E"]
[Contract "2C"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "E"]
1C 1H X pass 1NT pass 2C pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 2, chOption: E, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 2, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]
[VersionToken "6360b64575401540bf676df090fc74b794a2da7cee6a9d835b235a418f87fa2e"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/negative_doubles"]
[Student "S"]
{WEST has four \Ss, so instead of bidding them she makes a Negative Double.

EAST knows there is no 8-card fit in \Ss, but he does have \Hs 
stopped. He bids 1NT.

WEST has 9 points and with four \Cs she goes back to that suit and EAST passes.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "3"]
[Dealer "N"]
[Vulnerable "EW"]
[Deal "N:Q97.J87.AK6.KJT4 T5.Q542.QT85.853 AK632.93.972.Q92 J84.AKT6.J43.A76"]
[Declarer "S"]
[Contract "2S"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "N"]
1C 1H 1S pass 2S pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: S, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:2, nBasis: 0, nRot: 2, useStandardVul: true"]
[VersionToken "5b3d4d80fadd8e269c9c0f11980ed104a3634f523d44d6b8a1931c6c21ebf3d2"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/negative_doubles"]
[Student "S"]
{Compare this hand with Deal 6. 
SOUTH has five \Ss, this time so she bids 1\S.

NORTH knows there IS an 8-card fit in \Ss, so he bids 2\S.

SOUTH has 10 points so she passes.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "4"]
[Dealer "S"]
[Vulnerable "All"]
[Deal "S:KJ86.65.T832.873 A52.AQT93.97.AJ2 QT43.J2.AJ54.Q65 97.K874.KQ6.KT94"]
[Declarer "W"]
[Contract "4H"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "S"]
pass 1H 1S 2S pass 4H pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 4, chOption: W, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:3, nBasis: 0, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]
[VersionToken "3db651b94984ca4fc5fdf310e1d48ce6cf4958f9e9087f7d627215197941d2a5"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/negative_doubles"]
[Student "S"]
{EAST has 11/12 points, a Limit Raise in \Hs. So after the overcall 
he makes a Support Cue-bid of 2\S.

WEST adds her 16 to the 11 that EAST has promised as a minimum and goes straight 
to 4\H.

If EAST had significantly more than 11 he could bid on, but in this case he should happily pass.}

